Here are the **Maven commands** extracted from your document:

### Maven Installation

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install maven -y
mvn -version
```

### Create a Maven Project

```bash
mvn archetype:generate \
-DgroupId=com.example \
-DartifactId=my-app \
-DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart \
-DinteractiveMode=false
```

### Navigate to Project

```bash
cd my-app
ls
ls -R
```

### Build and Compile Project

```bash
mvn clean compile
```

### Run Java Application using Maven

```bash
mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.App"
```

### Package the Project

```bash
mvn package
```

### Run Generated JAR File

```bash
java -cp target/my-app-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar com.example.App
```

### Check Java Installation

```bash
java -version
```

### Maven Related Files/Directories

* `pom.xml` → Maven Project Object Model file
* `.m2` → Maven Local Repository directory

### Common Maven Lifecycle Commands

```bash
mvn validate
mvn compile
